00:26:49.019 --> 00:26:51.019
The Patterson Visitor Center

00:26:51.019 --> 00:26:53.019
is designed to be an immersive

00:26:53.019 --> 00:26:55.019
theocratic experience

00:26:55.019 --> 00:27:09.859
for everyone.

00:27:09.859 --> 00:27:11.859
The Patterson Visitor Center

00:27:11.859 --> 00:27:13.859
will feature three museums

00:27:13.859 --> 00:27:15.859
in this way.

00:27:15.859 --> 00:27:17.859
Our feature museum

00:27:17.859 --> 00:27:19.859
will be a first-century Bible village.

00:27:19.859 --> 00:27:26.779
The objective

00:27:26.779 --> 00:27:28.779
is to educate visitors

00:27:28.779 --> 00:27:30.779
about what life was like

00:27:30.779 --> 00:27:32.779
in the first century.

00:27:32.779 --> 00:27:34.779
And thereby, bring Bible accounts

00:27:34.779 --> 00:27:36.779
to life.

00:27:36.779 --> 00:27:38.779
You will get a sense of what things

00:27:38.779 --> 00:27:40.779
were like when Jesus walked the earth.

00:27:40.779 --> 00:27:42.779
Since the Israelites

00:27:42.779 --> 00:27:44.779
lived off the land,

00:27:44.779 --> 00:27:46.779
the experience begins

00:27:46.779 --> 00:27:48.779
with an overview of the annual crop

00:27:48.779 --> 00:27:50.779
cycles that form the core

00:27:50.779 --> 00:27:54.779
of so much of their daily activities.

00:27:54.779 --> 00:27:56.779
Key agricultural tasks,

00:27:56.779 --> 00:27:58.779
such as threshing, winnowing

00:27:58.779 --> 00:28:00.779
and grinding grain,

00:28:00.779 --> 00:28:02.779
will be illustrated

00:28:02.779 --> 00:28:06.509
with interactive displays.

00:28:06.509 --> 00:28:08.509
We know you will find the exhibit components

00:28:08.509 --> 00:28:10.509
like the functioning olive press

00:28:10.509 --> 00:28:12.509
and wine press,

00:28:12.509 --> 00:28:14.509
very interesting and informative.

00:28:14.509 --> 00:28:30.299
The next stop

00:28:30.299 --> 00:28:32.299
will be a typical first-century market.

00:28:32.299 --> 00:28:34.299
Here you will see some

00:28:34.299 --> 00:28:36.299
of the food and goods

00:28:36.299 --> 00:28:38.299
that would have been available

00:28:38.299 --> 00:28:40.299
depending on the season of the year.

00:28:40.299 --> 00:28:42.299
We next invite you

00:28:42.299 --> 00:28:44.299
into the residence

00:28:44.299 --> 00:28:46.299
and workshop spaces

00:28:46.299 --> 00:28:48.299
of a typical first-century

00:28:48.299 --> 00:28:50.299
Israelite family.

00:28:50.299 --> 00:28:53.710
The manger,

00:28:53.710 --> 00:28:55.710
carpentry shop,

00:28:55.710 --> 00:28:57.710
weaving and fabric-dying displays

00:28:57.710 --> 00:28:59.710
will illustrate a number

00:28:59.710 --> 00:29:01.710
of Israelite activities.

00:29:01.710 --> 00:29:03.710
The resident's courtyard area

00:29:03.710 --> 00:29:05.710
will show other regular home

00:29:05.710 --> 00:29:07.710
tasks like grain grinding

00:29:07.710 --> 00:29:09.710
and basket making.

00:29:09.710 --> 00:29:11.710
We next invite you

00:29:11.710 --> 00:29:13.710
into a typical Israelite home

00:29:13.710 --> 00:29:15.710
and out onto a rooftop

00:29:15.710 --> 00:29:17.710
overlooking the rest of the village.

00:29:17.710 --> 00:29:22.269
Before you leave the residences,

00:29:22.269 --> 00:29:24.269
you will also see an upper room

00:29:24.269 --> 00:29:26.269
that would have been

00:29:26.269 --> 00:29:28.269
in some of the Israelite homes.

00:29:28.269 --> 00:29:32.000
The next area

00:29:32.000 --> 00:29:34.000
of the first-century

00:29:34.000 --> 00:29:36.000
Bible village that you can explore

00:29:36.000 --> 00:29:40.619
is the synagogue,

00:29:40.619 --> 00:29:42.619
which was the center of worship

00:29:42.619 --> 00:29:44.619
and study in the Jewish community.

00:29:44.619 --> 00:29:46.619
Next, a functioning

00:29:46.619 --> 00:29:48.619
pottery wheel in kiln

00:29:48.619 --> 00:29:50.619
will illustrate how pottery was made.

00:29:50.619 --> 00:29:52.619
The last stop

00:29:52.619 --> 00:29:54.619
will take you to a lake side

00:29:54.619 --> 00:29:56.619
where you will be able to board

00:29:56.619 --> 00:29:58.619
a first-century fishing boat

00:29:58.619 --> 00:30:00.619
similar to the one

00:30:00.619 --> 00:30:02.619
that Jesus and His disciples used.

00:30:02.619 --> 00:30:04.619
Here you can learn

00:30:04.619 --> 00:30:06.619
what was involved in commercial fishing.

